# UI Figma Implementation Rules

- Match Figma desktop 1:1 first, then handle mobile.
- Map each Figma node to explicit JSX elements and stable CSS classes.
- Keep text content in translations (`sr.json`, `en.json`), not hardcoded in `App.tsx`.
- Reuse one style system per section; keep repeated variants visually identical.
- For image framing, use `object-fit: cover` and adjust with `object-position` per panel when needed.

## Typography

- Use `Marcellus` for display/headline titles and `Inter` for body/captions.
- Define typography directly on target text classes (avoid relying only on inheritance).
- If Windows rendering appears heavier than Figma, prefer `font-weight: 300` for body copy in that block.
- For critical Figma text, set explicit `font-style`, `font-weight`, `font-size`, and `line-height`.

## CSS Accuracy and Hygiene

- Avoid broad selectors that override section-specific text (for example generic `... p` rules).
- Ensure interactive controls are visible/clickable with correct stacking (`z-index`).
- Keep selectors minimal; remove dead classes, duplicates, and obsolete comments after refactors.
- Keep visual output unchanged during cleanup.

## Validation Workflow

- After substantial UI edits, run lint checks and a production build.
- When a style looks wrong, inspect computed styles first and resolve override/specificity issues before changing layout values.
- Confirm referenced assets exist in `public/assets/figma` and are real exported images (not placeholder solids).
